What’s going on in your code
importScripts(...)

This pulls in Firebase’s JavaScript SDK inside your service worker (firebase-messaging-sw.js).

Service workers run separately from your web page and can respond to push events even if your site isn’t open.

firebase.initializeApp(...)

Initializes your Firebase app inside the service worker using your project’s config.

firebase.messaging()

Gets the Firebase Cloud Messaging instance.

messaging.onBackgroundMessage(...)

This is the event listener for background messages — these are push messages received when your page is not active (minimized or closed).

payload contains the data you sent from your backend with sendNotification.

self.registration.showNotification(...)

This is the actual line that makes the notification pop up in the OS notification tray.

Uses the title, body, icon, badge, and image from the FCM payload.